<strong>Entertainment</strong><br/>

Manistee, Michigan offers a variety of activities and entertainment to make your vacation memorable and fun. Well-knows fishing and tourist spot, it is located on the western shore of northern Michigan, captivating with its serene nature and hospitable small-town spirit. Sand dunes and bluff-lined beaches are just minutes away at Lake Michigan. You can hike, bike, or have a paintball battle with your team in the national forest. After your big catch is all packed away, enjoy an afternoon of golf, fresh local dining, town museum tours, or visit a local Little River Casino for a night out.<br/><br/>

<strong>Golfing</strong><br/>
Enjoy an afternoon at one of Manistee&acute;s golf courses after your fishing trip. Manistee National Golf Resort is a hot spot for a relaxing afternoon outing, with its own inn, a restaurant and indoor and outdoor swimming pools.<br/><br/>

